             An asset-backed trust is issuing
$500 million of bonds backed by Australian auto debt, according
to a person familiar with the transaction.  
 JPMorgan Chase & Co., Macquarie Group Ltd. and Royal Bank
of Scotland Group Plc are managing the sale for the so-called
Smart Trust, said the person, who declined to be identified
because terms arenâ€™t public.  
